Taiwan Stock Movers: Formosa Plastics, Mitac, PixArt Imaging

-- B y   A d e l a   L i n
-- 
2011-05-17T05:56:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-17/acer-cathay-financial-fubon-tsmc-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 1:30 p.m. in Taipei.  The Taiex Index dropped 27.62, or 0.3 percent, to 8,884.09,
the lowest close since April 20.  Formosa Plastics Group:  Formosa Plastics Corp. (1301)  (1301 TT)
gained 2.2 percent to NT$115.00 after the company said it
resumed production at some factories that were shut after a fire
at its Mailiao, Taiwan complex on May 12.  Formosa Chemicals &
Fibre Corp. (1326)  (1326 TT) advanced 0.9 percent to NT$108.50.  MSCI index revisions:  Mitac International Corp. (2315)  (2315 TT)
sank 4 percent to NT$10.90, the lowest closing price since
February 2009.  PixArt Imaging Inc. (3227)  (3227 TT) tumbled 5.7 percent
to NT$108.00, the biggest drop since March 15. Both stocks will
be removed from the MSCI Taiwan Index as of the close on May 31,
index provider MSCI Inc. said in a statement following a review.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adela Lin in Taipei at 
 alin95@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net . 